This paper focuses on improving the training of deep neural networks, which is a core topic in machine learning. The paper specifically addresses the optimization of weight matrices in deep networks, which is a common problem in deep learning research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with computer vision problems such as image classification and object detection, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new method for improving Batch Normalization, which is a common technique in neural network optimization, indicating that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents empirical results on benchmark datasets, which suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) may also be a relevant sub-category.
